```python
class CompletionView(QTreeView):
    # https://github.com/The-Compiler/qutebrowser/issues/117

    resize_completion = pyqtSignal()
    _connected = None  # Added a private attribute to store connection status

    def __init__(self, win_id, parent=None):
        super().__init__(parent)
```

The `self.connected` attribute was moved to an instance variable `_connected` within the class definition. This change ensures that `_connected` is not shared across instances of the class, adhering to object-oriented principles. Additionally, a private variable name is used to indicate that this attribute should be treated as internal to the class implementation.
